Sentencas: Core-shell nanoparticles of Au@Ni bimetal with the composition of Au:Ni = 85:15 was developed successfully by facile co-reduction and annealing synthesis route.
Titulo: The annealing influence on the microstructure and performance of Au@Ni core-shell bimetal as the cathode of low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The forming mechanism of the nano core-shell was proposed.
Titulo: The annealing influence on the microstructure and performance of Au@Ni core-shell bimetal as the cathode of low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The annealing conditions based on the morphology, microstructure and evolution of the core-shell structures were analyzed and revealed by scanning electron microscope in detail.
Titulo: The annealing influence on the microstructure and performance of Au@Ni core-shell bimetal as the cathode of low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The core-shell structures were well kept after the uniform films of Au85Ni15 were annealed on top of the GDC (Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95) electrolyte.
Titulo: The annealing influence on the microstructure and performance of Au@Ni core-shell bimetal as the cathode of low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The complex impedance of the symmetrical half cells of Au@Ni/GDC/Au@Ni was performed at 500 degrees C. Under the optimal annealing conditions, the area specific resistance for the cathode on top of GDC was 0.25 Omega cm(2) at 500 degrees C.
Titulo: The annealing influence on the microstructure and performance of Au@Ni core-shell bimetal as the cathode of low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: And the power density of the anode supported cell Au@Ni/GDC/-NiO with the optimal profile was 153, 292, 464, 590, and 835 m Wcm(-2) at 450, 475, 500, 525, 550 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: The annealing influence on the microstructure and performance of Au@Ni core-shell bimetal as the cathode of low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
